	"reading2",
	"Living in a multicultural society offers many benefits, but it also presents challenges. Countries like Canada and Australia have successfully created diverse communities where people from different cultures live together harmoniously.\n\nOne major advantage of multiculturalism is cultural enrichment. When people from various backgrounds share their traditions, cuisines, and customs, society becomes more interesting and vibrant. For example, in Toronto, you can experience food from over 200 countries. This diversity also promotes tolerance and understanding among different groups.\n\nHowever, integration can be difficult. Immigrants must learn a new language and adapt to different customs, which takes time and effort. Some people face discrimination, which makes them feel unwelcome. To address these issues, governments provide language classes and settlement services. Schools teach students about different cultures to promote respect from an early age.\n\nEnvironmental protection is also important in diverse societies. People should turn off lights when not needed and cut down on waste. Using public transportation instead of cars helps reduce carbon emissions. By working together, multicultural communities can create sustainable cities that benefit everyone.",
